{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":7893,"text":"Hi. My name is Marwa,\nand I'm an architect."},{"time":11167,"text":"I was born and raised in Homs,"},{"time":13017,"text":"a city in the central\nwestern part of Syria,"},{"time":15759,"text":"and I've always lived here."},{"time":17905,"text":"After six years of war,"},{"time":19501,"text":"Homs is now a half-destroyed city."},{"time":22001,"text":"My family and I were lucky;\nour place is still standing."},{"time":25152,"text":"Although for two years,\nwe were like prisoners at home."},{"time":28359,"text":"Outside there were demonstrations\nand battles and bombings and snipers."},{"time":34080,"text":"My husband and I used to run\nan architecture studio"},{"time":37156,"text":"in the old town main square."},{"time":39333,"text":"It's gone, as is most\nof the old town itself."},{"time":42685,"text":"Half of the city's other neighborhoods"},{"time":44590,"text":"are now rubble."},{"time":46414,"text":"Since the ceasefire in late 2015,"},{"time":48670,"text":"large parts of Homs\nhave been more or less quiet."},{"time":51609,"text":"The economy is completely broken,\nand people are still fighting."},{"time":55326,"text":"The merchants who had stalls\nin the old city market"},{"time":57827,"text":"now trade out of sheds on the streets."},{"time":60296,"text":"Under our apartment, there is a carpenter,"},{"time":62816,"text":"sweetshops, a butcher, a printing house,\nworkshops, among many more."},{"time":68251,"text":"I have started teaching part-time,"},{"time":70399,"text":"and with my husband,\nwho juggles several jobs,"},{"time":72937,"text":"we've opened a small bookshop."},{"time":74938,"text":"Other people do all sorts\nof jobs to get by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78803,"text":"When I look at my destroyed city,\nof course, I ask myself:"},{"time":82081,"text":"What has led to this senseless war?"},{"time":84778,"text":"Syria was largely a place of tolerance,"},{"time":87033,"text":"historically accustomed to variety,"},{"time":89097,"text":"accommodating a wide range\nof beliefs, origins, customs,"},{"time":92402,"text":"goods, food."},{"time":94315,"text":"How did my country --"},{"time":95504,"text":"a country with communities\nliving harmoniously together"},{"time":98226,"text":"and comfortable in discussing\ntheir differences --"},{"time":100741,"text":"how did it degenerate into civil war,\nviolence, displacement"},{"time":104850,"text":"and unprecedented sectarian hatred?"},{"time":108239,"text":"There were many reasons\nthat had led to the war --"},{"time":111071,"text":"social, political and economic."},{"time":113743,"text":"They all have played their role."},{"time":115331,"text":"But I believe there is one key reason\nthat has been overlooked"},{"time":119227,"text":"and which is important to analyze,"},{"time":121161,"text":"because from it will largely depend"},{"time":123511,"text":"whether we can make sure\nthat this doesn't happen again."},{"time":127372,"text":"And that reason is architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129818,"text":"Architecture in my country\nhas played an important role"},{"time":132423,"text":"in creating, directing and amplifying\nconflict between warring factions,"},{"time":136467,"text":"and this is probably true\nfor other countries as well."},{"time":139750,"text":"There is a sure correspondence\nbetween the architecture of a place"},{"time":143306,"text":"and the character of the community\nthat has settled there."},{"time":146711,"text":"Architecture plays a key role\nin whether a community crumbles"},{"time":150450,"text":"or comes together."},{"time":152060,"text":"Syrian society has long lived\nthe coexistence"},{"time":154589,"text":"of different traditions and backgrounds."},{"time":156969,"text":"Syrians have experienced\nthe prosperity of open trade"},{"time":159723,"text":"and sustainable communities."},{"time":161499,"text":"They have enjoyed the true meaning\nof belonging to a place,"},{"time":164594,"text":"and that was reflected\nin their built environment,"},{"time":167321,"text":"in the mosques and churches\nbuilt back-to-back,"},{"time":169813,"text":"in the interwoven souks and public venues,"},{"time":172084,"text":"and the proportions and sizes based\non principles of humanity and harmony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176948,"text":"This architecture of mixity\ncan still be read in the remains."},{"time":180384,"text":"The old Islamic city in Syria\nwas built over a multilayered past,"},{"time":184147,"text":"integrating with it\nand embracing its spirit."},{"time":186602,"text":"So did its communities."},{"time":188253,"text":"People lived and worked with each other"},{"time":190205,"text":"in a place that gave them\na sense of belonging"},{"time":192435,"text":"and made them feel at home."},{"time":194464,"text":"They shared a remarkably\nunified existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197748,"text":"But over the last century,"},{"time":199237,"text":"gradually this delicate balance\nof these places has been interfered with;"},{"time":203762,"text":"first, by the urban planners\nof the colonial period,"},{"time":206466,"text":"when the French went\nenthusiastically about,"},{"time":208704,"text":"transforming what they saw\nas the un-modern Syrian cities."},{"time":211986,"text":"They blew up city streets\nand relocated monuments."},{"time":216255,"text":"They called them improvements,"},{"time":218255,"text":"and they were the beginning\nof a long, slow unraveling."},{"time":221655,"text":"The traditional urbanism\nand architecture of our cities"},{"time":224569,"text":"assured identity and belonging\nnot by separation,"},{"time":227759,"text":"but by intertwining."},{"time":229537,"text":"But over time, the ancient became\nworthless, and the new, coveted."},{"time":233641,"text":"The harmony of the built environment\nand social environment"},{"time":236657,"text":"got trampled over\nby elements of modernity --"},{"time":239344,"text":"brutal, unfinished concrete blocks,"},{"time":241550,"text":"neglect, aesthetic devastation,"},{"time":244273,"text":"divisive urbanism that zoned\ncommunities by class, creed or affluence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249859,"text":"And the same was happening\nto the community."},{"time":252352,"text":"As the shape of the built\nenvironment changed,"},{"time":254971,"text":"so the lifestyles and sense\nof belonging of the communities"},{"time":258303,"text":"also started changing."},{"time":260038,"text":"From a register\nof togetherness, of belonging,"},{"time":262679,"text":"architecture became\na way of differentiation,"},{"time":265274,"text":"and communities started drifting apart"},{"time":267695,"text":"from the very fabric\nthat used to unite them,"},{"time":270690,"text":"and from the soul of the place that used\nto represent their common existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275441,"text":"While many reasons had led\nto the Syrian war,"},{"time":277854,"text":"we shouldn't underestimate\nthe way in which,"},{"time":279997,"text":"by contributing to the loss \nof identity and self-respect,"},{"time":283870,"text":"urban zoning and misguided,\ninhumane architecture"},{"time":287271,"text":"have nurtured sectarian\ndivisions and hatred."},{"time":290416,"text":"Over time, the united city\nhas morphed into a city center"},{"time":293829,"text":"with ghettos along its circumference."},{"time":296782,"text":"And in turn, the coherent communities\nbecame distinct social groups,"},{"time":300871,"text":"alienated from each other\nand alienated from the place."},{"time":305133,"text":"From my point of view,"},{"time":306515,"text":"losing the sense of belonging to a place"},{"time":308656,"text":"and a sense of sharing it\nwith someone else"},{"time":310852,"text":"has made it a lot easier to destroy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313196,"text":"The clear example can be seen\nin the informal housing system,"},{"time":316904,"text":"which used to host, before the war,\nover 40 percent of the population."},{"time":321424,"text":"Yes, prior to the war,\nalmost half of the Syrian population"},{"time":325258,"text":"lived in slums,"},{"time":326717,"text":"peripheral areas\nwithout proper infrastructure,"},{"time":329843,"text":"made of endless rows of bare block boxes"},{"time":332740,"text":"containing people,"},{"time":334192,"text":"people who mostly belonged\nto the same group,"},{"time":336351,"text":"whether based on religion,\nclass, origin or all of the above."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341772,"text":"This ghettoized urbanism\nproved to be a tangible precursor of war."},{"time":346430,"text":"Conflict is much easier\nbetween pre-categorized areas --"},{"time":349808,"text":"where the \"others\" live."},{"time":351750,"text":"The ties that used\nto bind the city together --"},{"time":354307,"text":"whether they were social,\nthrough coherent building,"},{"time":356991,"text":"or economic, through trade in the souk,"},{"time":359148,"text":"or religious, through\nthe coexistent presence --"},{"time":362058,"text":"were all lost in the misguided\nand visionless modernization"},{"time":365794,"text":"of the built environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367782,"text":"Allow me an aside."},{"time":369467,"text":"When I read about heterogeneous urbanism\nin other parts of the world,"},{"time":373674,"text":"involving ethnic neighborhoods\nin British cities"},{"time":376170,"text":"or around Paris or Brussels,"},{"time":378303,"text":"I recognize the beginning\nof the kind of instability"},{"time":381921,"text":"we have witnessed\nso disastrously here in Syria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386027,"text":"We have severely destroyed cities,"},{"time":388257,"text":"such as Homs, Aleppo,\nDaraa and many others,"},{"time":391462,"text":"and almost half of the population\nof the country is now displaced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395345,"text":"Hopefully, the war will end,"},{"time":397517,"text":"and the question that,\nas an architect, I have to ask, is:"},{"time":401341,"text":"How do we rebuild?"},{"time":403317,"text":"What are the principles\nthat we should adopt"},{"time":405977,"text":"in order to avoid repeating\nthe same mistakes?"},{"time":409099,"text":"From my point of view, the main focus\nshould be on creating places"},{"time":412662,"text":"that make their people feel they belong."},{"time":414854,"text":"Architecture and planning\nneed to recapture"},{"time":417373,"text":"some of the traditional values\nthat did just that,"},{"time":420301,"text":"creating the conditions\nfor coexistence and peace,"},{"time":423556,"text":"values of beauty\nthat don't exhibit ostentation,"},{"time":426848,"text":"but rather, approachability and ease,"},{"time":429237,"text":"moral values that promote\ngenerosity and acceptance,"},{"time":432768,"text":"architecture that is for everyone\nto enjoy, not just for the elite,"},{"time":436769,"text":"just as used to be in the shadowed alleys\nof the old Islamic city,"},{"time":440445,"text":"mixed designs that encourage\na sense of community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444326,"text":"There is a neighborhood here in Homs\nthat's called Baba Amr"},{"time":447589,"text":"that has been fully destroyed."},{"time":449714,"text":"Almost two years ago,\nI introduced this design"},{"time":452264,"text":"into a UN-Habitat competition\nfor rebuilding it."},{"time":455285,"text":"The idea was to create an urban fabric\ninspired by a tree,"},{"time":459647,"text":"capable of growing\nand spreading organically,"},{"time":462592,"text":"echoing the traditional bridge\nhanging over the old alleys,"},{"time":465838,"text":"and incorporating apartments,\nprivate courtyards, shops,"},{"time":469614,"text":"workshops, places for parking\nand playing and leisure,"},{"time":473011,"text":"trees and shaded areas."},{"time":475625,"text":"It's far from perfect, obviously."},{"time":477635,"text":"I drew it during the few hours\nof electricity we get."},{"time":480930,"text":"And there are many possible ways\nto express belonging and community"},{"time":484552,"text":"through architecture."},{"time":485727,"text":"But compare it with the freestanding,\ndisconnected blocks"},{"time":488795,"text":"proposed by the official project\nfor rebuilding Baba Amr."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492774,"text":"Architecture is not the axis\naround which all human life rotates,"},{"time":496406,"text":"but it has the power to suggest\nand even direct human activity."},{"time":501231,"text":"In that sense, settlement,\nidentity and social integration"},{"time":505407,"text":"are all the producer and product\nof effective urbanism."},{"time":509990,"text":"The coherent urbanism\nof the old Islamic city"},{"time":512970,"text":"and of many old European\ntowns, for instance,"},{"time":515890,"text":"promote integration,"},{"time":517647,"text":"while rows of soulless housing\nor tower blocks,"},{"time":520908,"text":"even when they are luxurious,"},{"time":522697,"text":"tend to promote isolation and \"otherness.\""},{"time":525958,"text":"Even simple things"},{"time":527232,"text":"like shaded places or fruit plants\nor drinking water inside the city"},{"time":531112,"text":"can make a difference\nin how people feel towards the place,"},{"time":534311,"text":"and whether they consider it\na generous place that gives,"},{"time":537524,"text":"a place that's worth keeping,\ncontributing to,"},{"time":540720,"text":"or whether they see it\nas an alienating place,"},{"time":543101,"text":"full of seeds of anger."},{"time":545291,"text":"In order for a place to give,\nits architecture should be giving, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550100,"text":"Our built environment matters."},{"time":552128,"text":"The fabric of our cities is reflected\nin the fabric of our souls."},{"time":556802,"text":"And whether in the shape\nof informal concrete slums"},{"time":559777,"text":"or broken social housing"},{"time":561427,"text":"or trampled old towns"},{"time":563210,"text":"or forests of skyscrapers,"},{"time":564980,"text":"the contemporary urban archetypes"},{"time":567107,"text":"that have emerged\nall across the Middle East"},{"time":569839,"text":"have been one cause of the alienation\nand fragmentation of our communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574971,"text":"We can learn from this."},{"time":576488,"text":"We can learn how to rebuild\nin another way,"},{"time":579365,"text":"how to create an architecture\nthat doesn't contribute only"},{"time":582706,"text":"to the practical and economic\naspects of people's lives,"},{"time":585687,"text":"but also to their social, spiritual\nand psychological needs."},{"time":590043,"text":"Those needs were totally overlooked\nin the Syrian cities before the war."},{"time":594575,"text":"We need to create again\ncities that are shared"},{"time":597342,"text":"by the communities that inhabit them."},{"time":599777,"text":"If we do so, people will not feel the need"},{"time":602690,"text":"to seek identities opposed\nto the other identities all around,"},{"time":606563,"text":"because they will all feel at home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610246,"text":"Thank you for listening."}]}]}